{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Peel and devein shrimp, reserve shrimp shells and refrigerate shrimp until needed. Place shrimp shells, 1 garlic clove and 1 oz olive oil into mixing bowl and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>, then sauté <b>10 min\/250°F\/speed <b>.","Add water and cook <b>10 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b>. Strain through a fine sieve, reserve liquid and discard solids. Rinse mixing bowl and mixing bowl lid.","Place onion, 2 garlic cloves and 2 oz olive oil into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 4<b>. Sauté <b>8 min\/250°F\/speed <b>.","Add squid, wine, paprika and parsley, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup on top of mixing bowl lid and cook <b>13 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <b>.","Add saffron and reserved shrimp broth, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup on top of mixing bowl lid and cook <b>3 min\/212°F\/\/speed <b>.","Add rice and salt, place Varoma into position, add reserved shrimp, secure Varoma lid and cook <b>13 min\/212°F\/\/speed <b>. Remove Varoma and set aside. Transfer risotto to a bowl and let sit 5 minutes. Divide between 15 small bowls and top each with one cooked shrimp. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["15 large shrimp","3 garlic cloves, divided","3 oz extra virgin olive oil, divided","28 oz water","6 oz red onion, quartered","10 ½ oz squid, sliced into rings (½ in.)","2 oz white wine","1 tsp smoked paprika","1 tsp dried parsley","1 pinch saffron threads","9 oz Arborio rice","1 tsp salt"]}],"id":"r212625","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-an2WPbBN22A\/XZMzjoBz5GI\/AAAAAAAAays\/LiVdJC8XzpMykSX8UUhJgz3ri_yp0skyQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_eYlzg_1C3Ht0Usjk.png","title":"Squid and Shrimp Risotto","publishedAt":"2017-08-11T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.4 g","fat":"5.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"14 g","calories":"558 kJ \/ 133 kcal"},"usefulItems":"fine sieve, small bowls, refrigerator","basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h","15 portions"]}